data.name: Delayx.ToolTip
data.value:
If you want to disable your Aimbot while you are aiming at your target you can set a delay. For example if you put in 1000 = 1000ms = 1second it will disable the aimbot for 1 second if you aim at your target. Use this if the Aimbot is too sticky for you.
Higher Values are more legit.

data.name: SmoothX.ToolTip
data.value:
Imagine a square that lies around your Enemy. You can enlarge this square with the "Pixel X" function to up and down.
As soon as your crosshair reaches this square, the conditions for "Aimbot-Target" will take effect. That means your Aimbot Smoothnes will be switch from the "Aimbot-Searching" to the "Aimbot-Target". (Also your "Delay" will activate as soon as you reach that Square)
Use this if you want to be able to move your crosshair freely on the Enemy as soon as you reach the opponent or this square with your crosshair.

data.name: Pingx.ToolTip
data.value:
Will shoot X Pixels before the crosshair reaches the Target.
Also increases the Area which is detected as Enemy by the Triggerbot.
(If your Triggerbot shoots to slow increase this values by 10-30 and decrease the Firerate)

data.name: label24.ToolTip
data.value:
Not a real Hitchance but works like it...
100 = 100% = It only shoots if the chance is 100% to hit the Enemy (Probably won't shoot at all, the chance that it will 100% hit is low)
10 = 10% = It shoots if the chance to hit the Enemy is 10 or higher (Will shoot fast and miss shots)
70-90 is optimal
